no spot of all the world my own

the sum of human bliss so small
gather bliss to see my fellows blessed
that happiest spot below , Who can direct , when all pretend to know

that happiest spot his own , Extols the treasures of his stormy seas , And his long night of revelry and ease ; The naked savage , panting at the line , Boasts of his golden sands and palmy wine , Basks in the glare , or stems the tepid wave , And thanks his gods for all the good they gave
The shuddering tenant of the frigid zone
the treasures of his stormy seas

Her uplands sloping deck the mountain's side , Woods over woods in gay theatric pride ; While oft some temple's mouldering top between , With venerable grandeur marks the scene
That proudly rise or humbly court the ground
To winnow fragrance round the smiling land

pity , justice , indignation start , Tear off reserve , and bare my swelling heart ; Till half a patriot , half a coward grown , I fly from petty tyrants to the throne
